						<summary>

						<p>Slab in the Harijan vāḍa.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">14th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record in Nagarī script is incomplete and damaged. Hence purport not clear. It refers to probably the rule of Suratāṇa Mahaṁmada and to Vēṇḍanūr (modern Beṇṇūr) and Sāṁgvi.</p>						

						<p>In the date portion only Śārvari, Āshāḍha. ba. 5, Friday is available. The cyclic year Śārvari occured twice during this century [Śaka 1222 and Śaka 1282].</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 14th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
